body:
> Having a long-running release branch ends up a bit messy with all the merging, particularly when files are added/deleted. 

@dsymonds how so? The method I described creates a single merge commit for each release, nothing more. I don't know why added/deleted files matter?

> This started as a documentation issue 

@davecheney actually it didn't start as a documentation issue. When we did the conversion to Git in the first place we wanted to make this work, but didn't think of a good way to do it at the time.

With that said, I do agree this is of limited utility, probably for a very small audience indeed.
